postgresql://: This specifies the dialect or driver to be used for the database connection. In this case, it indicates the PostgreSQL database driver.
: This part of the URL is the username used to authenticate when connecting to the PostgreSQL database.

-pass- : This seems to represent the password for the PostgreSQL user. Please note that it's generally not recommended to store passwords directly in code or plain text files for security reasons. It's advisable to use environment variables or a more secure method to manage credentials.
localhost: This is the hostname or IP address of the machine where the PostgreSQL database is running. In this case, it refers to the local machine.
practice: This part of the URL specifies the name of the PostgreSQL database you want to connect to. Replace practice with the actual name of your PostgreSQL database.
